The paper deals with the cluster-cumulant expansion (CCE) based on the fixed points of iterative belief propagation (IBP), which is a technique used in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.AI), and statistical inference (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the extension of CCE to generalized belief propagation (GBP), which is a popular algorithm in the field of data science (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper proposes a new method that improves upon the existing loop-series (LS) technique, which is commonly used in statistical physics (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT, cs.AI, and cs.LG, followed by cs.DS and cs.SI.
